snippet.textDisplay: The heck is your obsession with supressors? You are loosing out a lot on dps by doing so - dispersion reduction with compensators will mean you can fire next shot much faster on manually operated guns (like anvil, renegade) and keep your full auto on target for far longer without missing shots on a bettina for example, similarily it will also significantly increase how many shots out of your 3 round bursts from arpegio are hitting a target. Muzzle break is less critical on some guns, but it can still help a lot on guns that climb hard. Meanwhile a suppressor does almost nothing for you on any close range gun - players will know where you are anyway.
snippet.textOriginal: The heck is your obsession with supressors? You are loosing out a lot on dps by doing so - dispersion reduction with compensators will mean you can fire next shot much faster on manually operated guns (like anvil, renegade) and keep your full auto on target for far longer without missing shots on a bettina for example, similarily it will also significantly increase how many shots out of your 3 round bursts from arpegio are hitting a target. Muzzle break is less critical on some guns, but it can still help a lot on guns that climb hard. Meanwhile a suppressor does almost nothing for you on any close range gun - players will know where you are anyway.

What a night. Thanks dude.. who ever you were.
